The paper discusses the challenges and shortcomings of package managers in Free and Open Source Software distributions, which are primarily related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also touches upon the role of packages in the upgrade process, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and operating systems (cs.OS). Finally, the paper discusses potential solutions to the upgrade problems, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
